Ahoy there, me old mum!
Yer son, he feels glum.
Without my lull-a-by,
sleep-just-won't-come.

It just won't come...

But I ask this of ye: 
Can games sing like me?
Mar-i-o can't croon, bro!
Don't-ye-ag-ree?

Hey now, me boys,
with your trink-ets and toys...
Yar, I know Nin-ten-do
gives-ye-yer-joys.

I feel such low-down shame,
me lovely dear dame...
I'm a rat--I laughed at
yer-mum's-weird-name.

What a weird name...

I ain't no crummy creep
who lives in trash heaps!
I'm just one old sea-hun
who-needs-some-sleep.

This sweet young lass, 
so full of spunk an' sass,
over tea, she tells me
I-gots-no-class.

Me heart feels savage pangs
from love's wick-ed fangs.
I think oft of the soft
song-that-she-sang.

That song she sang...

But on briny sea swells,
me heart, it beats well.
Through sea air, I'll float
where me-soul-com-pels.

Life on the sea suits
a pirate like me.
A footpad like you, lad
ain't-so-luck-y.

A lone pebble slip-slides
beneath the cold tides. 
Its movement is-a-hint
where-love's-truth-hides.

There love's truth hides...

Fetch one for me young lad;
you won't be left sad!
Don't be slow or you know
I-might-get-mad!

Here, take good note:
What moves old Kapp'n's boat
be an iced, extra-nice
cu-cum-ber float.

Sure, they may seem real fierce,
all tent-a-cles and teeth.
Most of 'em got soft hearts.
They-be-real-sweet!

Sea monsters can be misunderstood,
and it's sad.
Known me some sea monsters,
and they ain't so bad!

I'm just practicin' kissin',
it's all for me sweetie pie.
But those stares! Oh those glares!
Neighbors must think I'm such a weird guy!

Sometimes I kiss me
own reflection in me window,
and sometimes me
neighbors walk by!

When I comes home from me trips
she's eaten all o' me chips.
All me cakes and snack packs!
Guess me junk food is really just fer her?

Me wife says she
don't like me goin' to sea.
She says that she miss-es me,
but-I-ain't-so-sure!

It's like I told me wife: 
it can't be all my fault. 
Some gen-ius made su-gar
look 'zactly like salt!

I baked a big cake
for me daugh-ter's birthday.
But she took one taste, 
and she ran a-way!

First there's me ship, then me car
then me bus-i-ness license too.
It's not fair! I don't care!
And-I-won't-pay.

If they tax this song...

I can't keep track
of all me lic-en-ses, man. 
It seems the gov-ern-ment can
charge me all-day-long!

While I do love me cukes,
they sure curl me flukes,
but now, please! Zu-cchi-nis
give-me-the-spooks.

Zu-cchi-ni spooks...

So do ye carp an' scream?
Or pursue yer dreams?
Ei-ther way, ye'll be swayed
by the wind's schemes.

The wind, she blows,
and yer boat, well, she goes.
Whar's it end? That depends.
No-bod-y knows.
